{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}} {{Politics}} '''House of Assembly''' is a name given to the [[legislature]] or [[lower house]] of a [[bicameral]] parliament. In some countries this may be at a [[subnational]] level.
Historically, in [[Kingdom of Great Britain|British]] [[crown colonies]] as the colony gained more internal [[responsible government]], the House of Assembly superseded the (usually unelected) [[Legislative Council]] as the [[Colonialism|colonial]] legislature, often becoming the lower house.
